// diagramType: flowchart-diagram
// Rendered with the eraser-diagrams skill (Eraser /render). Regenerate: feed this DSL to the Eraser MCP and export PNG (imageQuality 3, theme light).
title Model and effort map: which seat runs which model at which effort
direction down
colorMode pastel
typeface clean

Claude [color: "#7c3aed", label: "Claude Code: Opus 4.8 (pinned claude-opus-4-8, ADR-018), effort ultracode"] {
  Orchestrator [icon: command, color: "#7c3aed", label: "Orchestrator: plan, gates, fix, PR, report, merge-gate (inline 01,03,05,06,08,09)"]
  Implementer [icon: code, color: "#7c3aed", label: "implementer xN: TDD implementation (02)"]
  Verifier [icon: search, color: "#7c3aed", label: "verifier: diff vs plan (04, inherits orchestrator)"]
  Determinism [icon: lock, color: "#7c3aed", label: "determinism-auditor: services/ (04, conditional)"]
  SecuritySeat [icon: shield, color: "#7c3aed", label: "security-reviewer: secrets, parsing, API (04, conditional)"]
  E2E [icon: play, color: "#7c3aed", label: "e2e-tester: runtime verification (07)"]
  Grade [icon: bar-chart-2, color: "#7c3aed", label: "grade-auditor: CAS grade estimate"]
}
Codex [color: "#10a37f", label: "OpenAI Codex: gpt-5.5 (owner Codex Pro login), independent second model family"] {
  CodexReview [icon: eye, color: "#10a37f", label: "codex-reviewer: every PR review (04)"]
  DocReview [icon: file-text, color: "#10a37f", label: "final document and PDF review"]
  Curate [icon: edit, color: "#10a37f", label: "journal curation (tools/curate.sh)"]
  SecondOpinion [icon: check-circle, color: "#10a37f", label: "grade second opinion (/cas-audit)"]
}

Orchestrator > CodexReview: every PR gets an independent second-family review [color: gray]
